.<br><br>Valas, I don't know you, and I am not looking to start a war, but this is one issue that I am very firm on, and you will not change my mind on this. <br><br>By pursuing this argument, you are saying that only those in large guilds should be killing Gods. As the server continues to mature and more people reach planes levels, there will be more and more open raids. <br><br>As Niyara said &quot;I'm truly not trying to be a bitch here, but why don't you stop wasting time and energy on this battle that you cannot win, and start making arrangements to attend some of the Open Raids in question?&quot;<br><br>/agree Niyara <p><BODY LINK=#C9770 VLINK=#C9770 ALINK=#C9770><p><image src="http://www.geocities.com/starshinesmile/Mily3.jpg" border=0 width=95 height=150 align="left"><b><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="3" color="#003000"><B>Milynna Mayti'Dilaan</B></font></b><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" color="#00700"><br><I>Wanderer of 52 Harvests</font><br><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" color="#003000"><br>Lady of the House of Divindi<br>Member of the House of Mystery<br>Loyal to the House of the Warlock<br><br><A HREF="http://www.vanitey.com/apex/apex.swf">APEX</A><br><A HREF="mailto:milynna@mail.com">milynna@mail.com</A></font></I></p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umilynnamaytidilaan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Milynna Mayti Dilaan</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 1/27/01 2:19:09 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uveladorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veladorn</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 253<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/26/01 10:31:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=568.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My solution to solving the open raid problem</span><hr size=1> I truly belive that if the open raids are left unchecked, its going to lead to the breakdown of the calendar system on Luclin.  I see this happening already.  I'm baffled that nobody else sees it.  Basically at this point what I hear everyone saying is that it really does not matter if your guild has 3 reservations up, if you want to do something, just have someone post it as an open raid and let others come along to random loot.  This is a huge loophole in the calendar and I expect many are going to start fully exploiting it.<br><br>  As for being discriminatory to unguilded or in small guilds, absolutely I am.  I am a full supporter of the guild system and I'm not ashamed of it.  Small guilds can always do raids together.  The guild I'm in Triad went out and formed an alliance with Ministry of Mirth when our numbers dipped.  Other small guilds can do the same.  Unguilded folks, if they are decent folks can always get an invite from a guild, many guilds like Apex and Triad for example will eventually add that person to consideration for major loot items if they put enough time in.  I must admit though, I really like the idea of forcing players to join a guild if they want to have access to the better items in the game.  Guilds right now are our only form of government in Norrath.  I'm loathe to see that system destroyed.<br><br> <p>Valas Defai</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umareica.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mareica</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Regist