ne will kill it on Thursday.  He still died, he still dropped stuff, how is this &quot;being wasted?&quot;  IMO the odds of a god staying up overnight are generally pretty good on a weeknight as it takes so long to clear to them that people (Me!!!) are passing out from fatigue before Cazic drops.  Unless the raid consists entirely of unemployed individuals then staying up until 4 am is not really viable.  I don't know about the rest of you, but I work 7-5 monday through friday and I need my rest.  A sleepless Aenae is a cranky Aenae, infusions of diet pepsi notwithstanding.<br><br>3.  God drops are a joy to have and to hold, but they are NOT an entitlement.  If you need some piece of gear from the big oooogly one, well, keep trying til you get it.  Some people are saying they are getting screwed because the open raids are taking the prime God slots, but those same people aren't willng to go on the open raids because &quot;by the time we got to the God it would be 4 am!&quot;.  Well, either kill him at 4am or else hope he lives until the weekend is all I can really say.<br><br>4.  Almost every raid Triad-MoM hosts is semi-open.  We have a lot of younger people needing planar gear so we are doing some FoF/PoH raids after not going in a long time.  If you'd like to come the post under the relevant thread on our boards.  I can't promise you will come (lots of people is tough to manage) but we'll see.<br><br>In closing.  Yes I am seeing some examples of overbooking.  But hey folks - if they really are Open raids with signups available to all, then start going.<br><br>Absolutely last comment.  If you EVER, EVER send me a tell asking if the &quot;God is up&quot; or &quot;which mobs are you killing now&quot; and making a decision to come or not based on that one factor (Loot), you will be looked upon VERY unfavorably.  Either you want to come and help or you don't.<br><br>Nuff said.<br><br><br><br><br> <p><img src=http://www.geocities.com/aenae_luclin/Priestess_of_Luclin.JPG></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucyriccs.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cyricc S</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/29/01 7:40:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=568.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A few things...</span><hr size=1> The open raids have are subject to the same guidelines as the guild raids.  The problem is people might be seeing it as six Open raids, instead of as Mily hosting three and whoever else hosting one or two.<br><br>If you look at the days that most of these open raids take place, they are on weekdays.  If you look at the history of the calendar, these weekday slots were not utilized at all, and the mobs up there were being wasted.<br><br>From what I see, this all has to do with people now wanting to kill the gods.  This should probably be a &quot;Can We Reserve a God&quot; thread because that is the only thing most of the people posting against the open raids seem to care about.<br><br>But that's just my opinon.<br><br>-Cyricc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uozzlaar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ozzlaar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/29/01 9:34:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=568.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My solution to solving the open raid problem</span><hr s