n individual or group will book far more than their fair share of open planar dates.  For instance, where we're limited to 3 dates on the calendar, there is no such limitation on the individual; further, this limitation is really unenforceable, because nobody is going to want to take the time to watch every single name.  However, if we do make the sign-up process a little more public, even to the point of just posting who is going on what raid, there will at least be some accountability.  Abuses will still exist, but they will be made more public, and allow the Derises and Chakans to rip them apart in the flames section <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  I know I wouldn't want to subject myself to that kind of attention. <p><hr align="center" size="1"><FONT FACE="Arial" SIZE=2><center><IMG SRC="http://members.home.net/dondelinger/SS/sbvorpal4.gif"><BR><B>Stryke Repeatedly</B><BR>Non-Political Planar Hippie Warrior<BR><hr align="center" size="1" width="10%"><B>Glimpse Morningtide</B><BR>Early 40s Hippie Druid<BR><hr align="center" size="1" width="10%">Harried High Commander, Silent Sentinels<BR><A HREF = "http://www.silentsentinels.com" TARGET = "_blank">Come See Us!</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulordhavemercy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lord Have Mercy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 458<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/30/01 7:59:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=568.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://geocities.com/jd_lhm/bruchani.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A few things...</span><hr size=1> i wouldnt tear up nobody , cuz i don