nymore Open Raids...<br><br>I may get flamed for this, but I think if someone/some group of people wants to raid a plane, they should be able to do it all in guild, or tag along with a more mature guild. Such are the disadvantages of not being a member of a self sufficient guild. <br><br>Or, if you are a member of a self sufficient guild, (Sterm, IB) then you shouldnt be booking Open Raids. I mean WTF? You have a guild that can do the plane without assistance from others, why make it Open? (Obvious reason is to abuse the calendar, to get more chances at the god)<br><br>To close my rant, I just wanna say that there are too many open raids. There are currently like 10 guilds that can handle the planes with ease. Members of smaller or younger guilds reserving open raids are just clogging the air ways. Join another guild if your guild can't do it, or ask to attend as a guest.<br><br>Oh, and Mily/Nyrara (whatever);<br>EVERYONE DOES have a *right* to get epic items and planar gear. That does NOT mean they deserve it. Many of these open raids are only successful for one of two reasons; 1) Experienced people go along to help, or 2) The open raid leader is in a guild that could have done the raid themselves, and just sent along the people neccessary to complete it. <br>However, nearly everyone else, before these new up and comers, joined the guilds that could do the planes in order to get the gear. I know of a certain Shaman who was unguilded for an ETERNITY, but consistently showed up for raids and did his part. Before long, he was added to the normal loot cycle.<br><br>The only solution that I see here is either;<br> only let people who are not in planes capable guilds book open raids, or;<br> have no open raids whatsoever. Those who are in guilds incapable of doing a planes raid self sufficiently could either join a new guild, or ask a hosting guild to attend their raid.<br><br><br>Those are my thoughts... =p <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezbo